Jose Mourinho's 'outstanding' recruitment policy is the reason Chelsea are so far ahead of their Premier League rivals, Gary Neville has claimed.

The Portuguese manager's side beat restored their three-point lead at the top of the Premier League table on Monday night after beating Stoke City 2-0.

John Terry and Cesc Fabregas scored for the hosts while Nemanja Matic and Thibaut Courtois were again impressive for the Blues. 

