And Neville believes it is those recent additions to the squad that have elevated Chelsea to a level above their rivals.

Speaking to Sky Sports 1's Monday Night Football, Neville said: 'The recruitment of Jose Mourinho since he has come into Chelsea has been outstanding. Absolutely outstanding.

'He's identified what a team needs. Matic - straight in. Courtois - they brought him back. (Diego) Costa - a strong centre forward. Fabregas - they needed a little bit of creativity at times last season against teams that played with deep defences.

