'The blend of what Chelsea have at the moment is why they will be fighting for the league with (Manchester) City, and why those two are streets ahead of everyone else.'

While Neville didn't single out any clubs for criticism, he did have a message for managers looking to add to their ranks in January

He said: 'To play in the centre midfield in the Premier League in a 38-game season which is a battle to win it, to not think that you're going to need physicality  - you're not going to do it through just technical ability. You're going to need to dig in there and fight and battle.

